lony in 1639, was the founder of a large American family, which included Robert Treat Paine (1731–1814), one of the signers of the Declaration of Independence. See also   Paine  ."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William Pannell was born in 1225, in Donnington, Sussex, England, United Kingdom. He married Mary in 1250, in Donnington, Sussex, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"1225–":"1225–Surnud","1229–Female":"1229–Surnud","1251–Female":"1251–Surnud","1225–Male":"1225–Surnud","1225":"1225","1251":"1251","1250":"1250","1229":"1229","Donnington, , Somerset, England":"Donnington, Sussex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1225–":"1225–Kuollut","1229–Female":"1229–Kuollut","1251–Female":"1251–Kuollut","1225–Male":"1225–Kuollut","1225":"1225","1251":"1251","1250":"1250","1229":"1229","Donnington, , Somerset, England":"Donnington, Sussex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1225–":"1225–Décédé","1229–Female":"1229–Décédée","1251–Female":"1251–Décédée","1225–Male":"1225–Décédé","1225":"1225","1251":"1251","1250":"1250","1229":"1229","Donnington, , Somerset, England":"Donnington, Sussex, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"William Pannell est né en 1225, à Donnington, Susse